The user wants me to use a read-only tool from github-local. Looking at the available tools, the read-only options are:
- github-local.get_file - Read the contents of a file in a repo
- github-local.get_repo_info - Get repo metadata
- github-local.list_branches - List branches in a repo
- github-local.list_files - List files/directories at a path in a repo
- github-local.list_issues - List issues in a repo
- github-local.search_code - Search code across GitHub

I'll use one of these. Let me start with getting repo info for a common repository to demonstrate the read-only tool. I'll use a well-known public repo like "octocat/Hello-World" or similar.

Actually, let me use github-local.get_repo_info to get information about a repository. I'll use a public repo.


{
  "tool_calls": [
    {
      "tool": "github-local.get_repo_info",
      "arguments": {
        "owner": "octocat",
        "repo": "Hello-World"
      }
    }
  ]
}
